Median notochaetae arranged in longitudinal short series; all notochaetae multiarticulate capillaries, most chaetae with short articles basally and medially, medium-sized or long distally, one chaetae with long articles basally (
Fig. 26E
), 4–6 per ramus, 1/6 as long as body width. Aristate neurospines from chaetiger 2, most broken, arranged in J-shaped patterns, 4–5 per ramus (
Fig. 26F
); neurochaetae with very short rings, tips broken, visible in juvenile or smaller specimens (
Fig. 26G
).
